      <para id="id6346003">In contrast with PTFE, octafluoroisobutylene, (CF<sub>3</sub>)<sub>2</sub>C=CF<sub>2</sub>, is highly toxic, while perfluorodecahydronapthalene (C<sub>10</sub>F<sub>8</sub>, <link target-id="id6144790"/>) is used as a blood substitute component. </para>


      <figure id="id6144790"><media id="id6144790_media" alt="">
